==Awards== 
{{main|FIFA World Cup awards}}
At the end of each World Cup finals tournament, awards are presented to the players and teams for accomplishments other than their final team positions in the tournament. There are currently six awards: 
*The ''[[adidas]] [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Shoe - Top Goalscorers|Golden Shoe]]'' for the top goalscorer (formerly called the ''Golden Shoe'', or sometimes, the ''Golden Boot'', first awarded in [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]); most recently, the ''Silver Shoe'' and the ''Bronze Shoe'' have been awarded to the second and third top goalscorers respectively;
*The ''[[adidas]] [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Ball|Golden Ball]]'' for the best player, determined by a vote of media members (formerly called the ''Golden Ball'', first awarded in [[1982 FIFA World Cup|1982]]); the ''Silver Ball'' and the ''Bronze Ball'' are awarded to the players finishing second and third in the voting respectively;
*The ''[[FIFA World Cup awards#Yashin Award|Yashin Award]]'' for the best goalkeeper (first awarded in [[1994 FIFA World Cup|1994]]); 
*The ''[[FIFA World Cup awards#FIFA Fair Play Trophy|FIFA Fair Play Trophy]]'' for the team with the best record of fair play (first awarded in [[1978 FIFA World Cup|1978]]); 
*The ''[[FIFA World Cup awards#Most Entertaining Team|Most Entertaining Team]]'' award for the team that has entertained the public the most during the World Cup, as determined by a poll of the general public (first awarded in [[1994 FIFA World Cup|1994]]); 
*The ''[[FIFA World Cup awards#Best Young Player Award|Gillette Best Young Player]]'' award for the best player at most 21 years of age at the start of the calendar year (first awarded in [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]]).
An ''[[FIFA World Cup awards#All-Star Team|All-Star Team]]'' consisting of the best players of the tournament is also announced for each tournament since [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]].

