===FIFA World Cup winning captains and managers===
[[Franz Beckenbauer]], with [[Germany national football team|West Germany]], is the only person to date who has won the World Cup as both captain (1974) and head coach (1990). [[Mário Zagallo]], with [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], also won the World Cup as both player (1958 and 1962) and head coach (1970). [[Italy national football team|Italy]]'s [[Vittorio Pozzo]] is the only head coach to ever win two World Cups.  All World Cup winning head coaches were natives of the country  they coached to victory. 

